node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we’re talking to @leah__ring, co-founder and creative director of L.A.’s @anotherhumandesign. node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we spoke to @bimmawilliams, co-founder and host of the @claimastories podcast. Claima — ”claima” as in “claim a seat at the table” — is a podcast with a mission: to give young BIPOC creatives the inspiration, and roadmap, they need to make good on their ambitions. Bimma joins us from the road — specifically from, a custom-rigged 1993 Mitsubishi Delica Starwagon rechristened as “Storytella,” his mobile podcast studio during a 30-day, four-city tour of the West Coast. Here, he gives his best advice for young BIPOC creatives looking for professional advancement and shares a few of the stories that have moved him most. \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.title: DMTV Milkshake: Making Space for BIPOC Creatives

🔄 Rotate Your Device 🔄
Inside the Dallas studio of sculptor Dan Lam (@sopopomo), burbling, bubbling and bright works of art appear to move on their own. Commissioned by @Genesis_usa, the artist transformed her distinct style into her first-ever digital art car and NFT inspired by her time in the G70. Lam took inspiration from her time driving the G70, and worked with digital designer Stephen Judge (@stephenthejudge) to bring her vision of the world passing outside the windows to life. #G70artcars #GenesisG70 #G70 #artcars #digitalartcars #NFTs #BorntoMove

node.title: Sculptor Dan Lam Blends the Outside World into Her Genesis G70 Art Car

node.text: The latest collection from @tsarcarpets, dubbed the Forma Collection, is their largest yet. node.text: Float tanks have grown in popularity over the years for their ability to destress and detoxify the body. For the uninitiated, float tanks allow you to float in salted water without *any* sensory stimulation from the outside world. And for those who have visited a float tank spa in the past, you know there’s usually nothing remarkable about the environment. BUREAU (helmed by @daniel_zamarbide), however, is changing that for the better with Floating Realities, a float tank spa project in Geneva, Switzerland. \\\ Read more about the revolutionary new Floating Realities at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Summer is the perfect time to get a little daring with your decor, and this month we’re feeling inspired by all things Bright + Bold – saturated colors, bold palettes and graphic elements – for their energetic feel. Of course we can’t think of the words “bright” and “bold” without lifestyle brand Poketo coming to mind. Husband-and-wife team Ted Vadakan and Angie Myung wanted to infuse art and design into their every day lives, so they began creating collections of design-conscious products infused with juicy colors and patterns to make it a reality. From their popular paper goods to their fun dinnerware, the brand radiates happiness and joy, so we've rounded up some of our favorite Poketo products for adding a vibrant twist to your home. \\\ Shop the full roundup at the link in bio! 🔗

node.text: Designed by architects Bruna Louise and Arthur Mansur of @momba.arq, the Table Cápsula was made to accommodate the needs of those who work from home and provide a solution for separating work life from home life. The table functions as a writing desk that, after putting the “office” away into the drawers, can be used as a console table or sideboard. The single metallic structure, originally inspired by Marcel Breuer’s classic Cesca chair, is offered in four different colors. The table top with drawers is also available in three different finishes, allowing for metal and wood to be mixed and matched for a custom look. \\\ Read more about the Table Cápsula at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Dutch brand @red_stitch_furniture enlisted the creative mind of designer @florishovers back in 2019 to, in their words, "release all conventions and create a new sofa sprung from his free creative mind.” The design process didn’t begin where it normally does–with sketches–and instead, Floris made a miniature sofa from found materials in his Raamsdonksveer workshop. “Most designers start from an upholstery point of view. I wanted to start with the frame as a focal point,” says Floris. The FLOAT Collection has officially launched and, in this month’s Deconstruction, we’re sharing Hovers’ unconventional design process. \\\ At the link in bio, read on about the making of the FLOAT collection and Floris Hovers' partnership with Red Stitch.
